  position: relative;
  min-height: 1px;
  padding-right: .9375rem;
  padding-left: .9375rem;
}
```

This would also allow us to use `.{size}-{n}` (and the related offsets, pushes, and pulls) for things other than columns (e.g. form groups where we might not want the min-height, position, and/or padding of columns).

In v3, I'm currently using the following additional responsive utilities, and I was hoping to get your opinion/approval for making it into a feature of v4. Bootstrap currently has the following responsive utility classes:

``` css
.visible-xs-*
.visible-sm-*
.visible-md-*
.visible-lg-*
.hidden-xs
.hidden-sm
.hidden-md
.hidden-lg
