Guys,

One of the most common hacks I have to make is adjusting the widths on the dl-horizontal class, usually for smaller spaces but it would make sense to have a larger one for larger date formats. I'm happy for you to reject or change, but I feel like this should be a part of the core. It could also be provided via mixin but I'm not as certain it needs it as much.

This will allow for DT widths of 60px, 160px (default) and 260px.
Also, you'll be able to use the dl-horizontal in containers such as col-lg-3 etc...

``` sass
.dl-horizontal {
  dd {
    @include clearfix(); // Clear the floated `dt` if an empty `dd` is present
  }

    @media (min-width: $grid-float-breakpoint) {
        dt {
            float: left;
            width: ($component-offset-horizontal - 20);
            clear: left;
            text-align: right;
            @include text-overflow();
        }
        dd {
            margin-left: $component-offset-horizontal;
        }
    }
    &.dl-horizontal-sm {
        @media (min-width: $grid-float-breakpoint) {
            dt { width: ($component-offset-horizontal - 100); }
            dd { margin-left: ($component-offset-horizontal - 90); }
        }
    }
    &.dl-horizontal-lg {
        @media (min-width: $grid-float-breakpoint) {
            dt { width: ($component-offset-horizontal + 80); }
            dd { margin-left: ($component-offset-horizontal + 90); }
        }
    }
}
```

Alternatively you could use a mixin like:

``` sass
@mixin createInlineDefinitionList($component-dt-width:160px) {
    @media (min-width: $grid-float-breakpoint) {
            dt { width: $component-dt-width; }
            dd { margin-left: ($component-dt-width + 10); }
    }
}
.dl-horizontal {
    dd {
        @include clearfix(); // Clear the floated `dt` if an empty `dd` is present
    }

    @media (min-width: $grid-float-breakpoint) {
        dt {
            float: left;
            clear: left;
            text-align: right;
            @include text-overflow();
        }
    }
    &.dl-horizontal-sm { @include createInlineDefinitionList(60px); }
    &.dl-horizontal-md { @include createInlineDefinitionList(160px); }
    &.dl-horizontal-lg { @include createInlineDefinitionList(260px); }
}
```

