However as of `3.0.3` this functionality no longer works and the documention states that nested containers are not supported due to hard coded width's on container media query.

I was able to get this working by creating CSS for `.container-nested`, which duplicates everything from `.container`, apart from the media queries;

```
.container-nested {
  padding-right: 15px;
  padding-left: 15px;
  margin-right: auto;
  margin-left: auto;
}

.container-nested:before,
.container-nested:after {
  display: table;
  content: " ";
}

.container-nested:after {
  clear: both;
}

.container-nested:before,
.container-nested:after {
  display: table;
  content: " ";
}

.container-nested:after {
  clear: both;
}
```

